Service method logic is stored in domain layer. In that
case we have fvacade here, and all required
dependencies to execute this logic are injected in Core
layer. UI Layer has an access to Core Layer
Speciﬁc user action will execute one of injected domain services method. Input
data will be provided through Request Object. Output data will be domain
model which can be translated to UI model if needed. Once you receive output
data from domain you can transform it to any structure depending on external
Sometimes we can reuse domain model
if response is in the same structure but
it's recommended to map domain model
to ui model and apply transformations
User interface layer is just an input layer for multiple protocols of
communication or multiple ways of communicating with server. It can be
communication based on Web like GrqphQL, REST or it can be CLI app - from
architectural point of view it doesn't really matter.
